			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">8) Revamp pet focus availability. (Pet Issues/Requests) [updated request] 
<br />
- Changed request, since off-tanking is too broad a term, and related to too many factors besides the pet itself </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This I think is a very important point.  When you look at mage progression, we get:
<br />

<br />
Original through Velious:
<br />
- Temple of Sol Ro quests - doable by the appropriate levels
<br />
- Staves of Elemental Mastery - drops/quests in the "end zones" for this period (Plane of Hate, Plane of Sky, Phinigel Autropos).
<br />

<br />
Luclin:
<br />
- GoDS - from end zone (Vex Thal)
<br />

<br />
PoP:
<br />
- SoAS - from end zone (PoTime)
<br />

<br />
LDoN:
<br />

<br />
- DPoC - 760 points in NRo
<br />
- (not sure on name) equivalent to VT focus in raid adventure
<br />

<br />
Now, it is obvious that raiding is the end-game of EQ.  However, it should not be impossible for a non-raiding mage to increase their pet power through hard work.  Even the raiding mages are forced to progress through content without getting gear that can improve 40% or so of their damage output, until they make it to the end zones where they can finally upgrade their pet side, with one particular item.
<br />

<br />
There are a few possibilities here.  Add a Ritual Summoning (VT focus) item to the Ssra Temple drop tables, perhaps from the Rhags.  This item would have low stats, nothing to compare with the GoDS, so the GoDS are still an upgrade despite the focus remaining the same.
<br />

<br />
Likewise on the Time focus.  The elemental planes should have a *mancy focus appropriate to the plane which focuses that style of pet to the level of a Time focused pet.  The items would have Elemental-level stats, and would only focus one of our 4 types of pets.  The items should be for different slots from each other, or at least complementary (bracers, rings, earrings) so that a mage could in theory have all 4 foci available at the same time if they wanted.  If they dropped from the raid-level minis in the proper zones, they should be at the proper point for progression purposes.
<br />

<br />
For LDoN and the non-raiding mages, perhaps add a VT level focus buyable for 1492, and a Time level single-element (*mancy) focus at ~2000.  This gives non-raiders something to aim for while not taking away the raiding focus of the end-game.
<br />

<br />
Pet foci are as important to mages as aggro weapons and Anger3 augs are for warriors, or a good bow is to a ranger.  There should be a progression rather than have the current foci only drop in the expansion's end zones.  Mages need to build their power to progress like any other class.
<br />

<br />
Another possibility:  Make *mancy an AA purchase which is a <span style="font-weight: bold">stackable</span> focus for an elemental type.  20AAs wouldn't be unreasonable for the ability to summon a more effective pet than the standard.  It wouldn't remove the need for gear upgrades, by itself it would be roughly where DPoC focused pets are (possibly without the regen and auto-equipped armour).  Maybe something like +1 level, +500hp, +4 to max hit, +25 attack, maybe a specific effect by element type as well.  Nothing amazing, but enough to make a visible difference in DPS and survivability.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fazzadien Elementweaver</a> 
<br />
Arch Convoker (on sabbatical)
<br />
Not guild affiliated - Kane Bayle server
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red"><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">Free at last of the addiction that is MMORPG, but yes, I still enjoy it when I do manage to sit and play!</span></span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
