				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello fellow mages, I am a LONG time lurker here in the forum, but this
<br />
will be my first post. I think what I'm about to mention is close to the pet
<br />
off-tanking ability, but needs to be more.
<br />

<br />
Here is my senerio:
<br />
You have entered Plane of Nightmare
<br />
/pet attack
<br />
Attacking a raven master
<br />
/cast 2
<br />
A raven has been hit for 1530 non-melee damage
<br />
(thinks to himself ooh, look, I can solo this...er..uh...damn, pet dead,
<br />
better run)
<br />
Loading Please Wait...
<br />

<br />
Yes, this really happened to me by the way! Pey was ay 10% by the time
<br />
I got 1 nuke off. He was fully equipped and buffed. 
<br />

<br />
Now, I'm not saying I should be able to solo any zone etc etc, but what I
<br />
am saying is: If I can kill MOB X with my mana pool and spells, then my
<br />
pet should be able to survive that fight long enough for me to nuke it to
<br />
death. This is not the case for me. I am an average geared mage. I have 
<br />
DPoC, mostly Velious and Luclin gear, some pre-elemental PoP gear, etc, 
<br />
but that says nothing for my pet's ability to live long in a fight. Mages 
<br />
should not have to be healers. We should never have gotten a pet heal. 
<br />
Our pets should be out shields, our way out of death that every other 
<br />
caster has. I cannot FD, mez, or anything else, but my pet should not be 
<br />
killed like he is wearing the same robe that I am!
<br />

<br />
Everyone seems to be asking for pet damage increase and sure, that's 
<br />
gonna help in groups where pet is not being damaged, but what about the 
<br />
solo mage? Or being able to use my pet as MT in groups. With a good 
<br />
healer I have been able to use my pet in normal LDoNs as MT, but surely 
<br />
not hards.
<br />

<br />
OK, I'll stop now, but I do hope someone gets my point, and I hope to be 
<br />
posting here more now!
<br />

<br />
Thanks to all who are helping with the mage balancing!<br />_________________<br />Zephar Gatecaller
<br />
Epic Magician of Quellious
<br />
Brothers of Darkness
<br />
