				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">hehe sorry for the delay in my post, but have been busy...
<br />
Yes, I meant "Attacking a raven, master", and yes, my pet cannot tank it long enough for me to nuke it down.
<br />

<br />
   Same thing goes for trash in almost all the PoP zones. I can solo some in PoD, and pretty much own PoJ, but when it comes to say, PoV, HoH, PoTorment, etc, my pet just cannot tank for me. I can tell when I nuke these trash MOBs and they drop 5-10% HP that I COULD solo them if my pet would live. A Wiz can root, a necro can fear, and several other classes have ways to keep these MOBs off them so they can use their mana to actually do the DPS to kill the MOB.
<br />
   We need a pet similar to Decoy, but one that does, say, half the DPS, but has some insane AC and HP so that he simply taunts and allows us to nuke. A pet that can keep a mage alive in the zones he fights in.
<br />
   As has been said a hunderd times before, mages have no root, no snare, no FD, we are the only class without such an "escape" that is unique. A pet such as this would not add to our DPS, but it would do wonders for survivability.
<br />
   Getting long winded here, so I'll leave it at that. Thanks to everyone for helping us mages get some much needed changes made.<br />_________________<br />Zephar Gatecaller
<br />
Epic Magician of Quellious
<br />
Brothers of Darkness
<br />
The Nameless</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
